Setting up the TabularDataLoader

The data loader is required to feed data into the learner during training

procs = [Categorify, FillMissing, Normalize]

with open(model_data_path, "rb") as f:
    to = pickle.load(f)

Get splits object for TabularPandas

Creating the data loader

dls = to.dataloaders()

Setting up the Learner

The main function to set up a learner for tabular data is fastai's tabular_learner function, which is based on the Learner class.

mish[source]

mish(x)

class Mish[source]

Mish() :: Module

Same as nn.Module, but no need for subclasses to call super().__init__

Modifying the TabularModel class so it can take any non-linear activation functions

Setting up the customized tabular learner

%%time
learn = tabular_learner(dls, n_out=1, loss_func=loss_fun, config=dict(active_fun=Mish),
                        y_range=y_range)

CPU times: user 10.4 ms, sys: 7.66 ms, total: 18 ms
Wall time: 18.3 ms
